               <head>Masnavi-'i ma'navi, book IV</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Mas̲navī-'i maʿnavī by Jalāl al-Dīn Rūmī</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85100085 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2002005579 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85129656" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_3666-item1">
                     <note>
                        <p>Didactic mas̲navī on Islamic wisdom and spirituality, containing book 4, in 2 columns, beginning f. 8v</p>
                        <p>Poem prefixed by list of contents (ff. 2r-7v) and verses ascribed to Saḥābī with additional Gujarati numbers (f. 1v)</p>
                        <p>Selected verses ascribed to Saḥābī and Jāmī at end (f. 142r)</p>
                        <p>Dated (f. 141v): completed salkh (=end) Z̲ī al-qaʿdah 1084/8 March 1674</p>
                        <p>Seal impression (f. 8r), rounded naskh in interlacing looped ṭughrā formation: Muḥammad bin Muḥ[y]ī al-Dīn 1165/1751-2</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="guj">Persian &amp; Gujarati</textLang>
